description: {"blocks":[{"key":"7s30k","text":"This protocol was described in the paper “Nested PCR Approach for petB Gene Metabarcoding of Sorted Marine Synechococcus Populations”. The objective was to create a nested PCR approach for amplifying the petB (encoding the cytochrome b6 subunit of the cytochrome b6f complex) marker gene from marine Synechococcus populations. The protocol can be used with DNA templates from samples obtained by traditional filtration methods as well as flow cytometry sorting, which often have low nucleic acid concentrations. We suggested that our protocol would be of interest to those applying flow cytometry for cell physiology measurements, such that these studies can also obtain the community composition simultaneously.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":65,"length":5},{"style":"italic","offset":107,"length":13},{"style":"italic","offset":204,"length":4},{"style":"italic","offset":300,"length":14},{"style":"sub","offset":235,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":264,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1370h","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eook1","text":"This protocol has two parts: ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3mapp","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d5hl1","text":"1) The steps used to extract the DNA from filtered marine seawater samples and flow cytometry sorted samples.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"705hi","text":"2) Standard and nested PCR amplification reactions of the petB marker gene.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":58,"length":4}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9824l","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
